def preparerate(val):
    if(val=='NEW' or val =='-'):
        return np.nan
    else:
        val=str(val).split('/')
        val=val[0]
        return float(val)

df['rate']=df['rate'].apply(preparerate)

def handlecomma(val):
    val=str(val)
    if ',' in val:
        val=val.replace(',' , '')
        return float(val)
    else:
        return float(val)

df['cost2plates']=df['cost2plates'].apply(handlecomma)
df['cost2plates'].unique()
